==English==

===Verb===
to '''[[rough up]] the [[bullpen]]'''

# (''baseball'') In baseball, the act of the offensive team being able to easily hit pitching by the starting and relief pitchers of the opposing team, despite the types of pitches thrown.
#: ''The strong baseball team really '''roughed up the bullpen''' in their 34-0 rout against their foes; the coach used nine relievers and they still couldn't get anybody out.''